WEBVTT

00:00:01.587 --> 00:00:03.423
[ALL]
Thank you for the food!

00:00:03.507 --> 00:00:06.513
[ALAS RAMUS]
Thank you for the food!

00:00:06.597 --> 00:00:07.431
[ALAS RAMUS gobbling]

00:00:09.435 --> 00:00:11.356
Mama! Tofu me!

00:00:11.439 --> 00:00:13.945
[EMI]
You got it! Comin' right up.

00:00:14.947 --> 00:00:16.867
[gasps] Bad! Mine!

00:00:16.951 --> 00:00:18.370
Don't blame me.

00:00:18.453 --> 00:00:21.167
I told Alciel to leave
the ginger bud off mine.

00:00:21.251 --> 00:00:23.631
He knew I was going to be
sharing with Alas Ramus.

00:00:23.714 --> 00:00:24.883
Mmm-hmm.

00:00:24.967 --> 00:00:25.927
I'm helping.

00:00:26.010 --> 00:00:29.141
Nobody likes a picky eater,
so I'm saving her the hardship.

00:00:29.225 --> 00:00:30.687
Thoughtful, but still.

00:00:30.770 --> 00:00:33.985
I think ginger buds may be
a little too intense for a baby.

00:00:34.068 --> 00:00:35.530
Preach, sister.

00:00:35.613 --> 00:00:37.408
It's too intense for me, too.

00:00:37.491 --> 00:00:38.577
No surprise.

00:00:38.661 --> 00:00:40.205
You're quite
the infant yourself.

00:00:40.289 --> 00:00:42.126
To be frank,
they're a bit much for me, too.

00:00:42.209 --> 00:00:43.921
Say it's not so, Sire!

00:00:44.005 --> 00:00:47.011
[NEWSCASTER 17A] <i>In other news,
firework season is upon us.</i>

00:00:47.094 --> 00:00:47.929
<i>Chances are,</i>

00:00:48.013 --> 00:00:50.392
<i>there will be a spectacular show
in your area.</i>

00:00:50.475 --> 00:00:51.812
[SUZUNO]
A refined custom.

00:00:51.895 --> 00:00:54.025
I'd love to experience it
in the flesh.

00:00:54.108 --> 00:00:55.695
[URUSHIHARA]
You can count me out.

00:00:55.778 --> 00:00:57.072
Too many people.

00:00:57.156 --> 00:00:59.661
[ASHIYA] I would not take you
even if you begged me.

00:00:59.745 --> 00:01:00.997
-[URUSHIHARA] Huh? Why not?
-[ALAS giggling]

00:01:01.080 --> 00:01:02.625
[ASHIYA] You know good
and well why not!

00:01:02.709 --> 00:01:04.504
[ALAS]
Mmm.

00:01:05.548 --> 00:01:06.800
[MAOU]
Can I help you?

00:01:13.021 --> 00:01:14.023
[EMI]
Don't freak out,

00:01:14.106 --> 00:01:16.027
but, I'm gonna stay
at my parents' place

00:01:16.110 --> 00:01:16.945
for a while.

00:01:17.572 --> 00:01:18.616
[ALL]
Huh?

00:01:20.035 --> 00:01:21.955
Me and mama gonna go!

00:02:54.849 --> 00:02:55.893
This trip.

00:02:55.977 --> 00:02:57.522
So, what was the impetus?

00:02:57.605 --> 00:02:59.776
[MAOU, CHIHO]
Um...

00:03:00.987 --> 00:03:03.534
I'm just sick of not knowing
what to do.

00:03:03.617 --> 00:03:04.953
♪

00:03:05.036 --> 00:03:08.042
My life's purpose
was to defeat the Devil.

00:03:08.126 --> 00:03:10.422
But then, Alas Ramus showed up,

00:03:10.506 --> 00:03:13.554
and things got a hell
of a lot more complicated.

00:03:14.054 --> 00:03:16.183
And now we've got
all these angels and demons

00:03:16.267 --> 00:03:18.939
coming out of the woodwork,
and stirring up trouble.

00:03:20.108 --> 00:03:22.321
To be honest,
I'm fed up with these randos

00:03:22.404 --> 00:03:23.824
messing with my life.

00:03:23.908 --> 00:03:25.076
It's an ass whip.

00:03:25.995 --> 00:03:29.293
I need a break, so I might
as well go to Ente Isla.

00:03:29.376 --> 00:03:31.047
If I retrace Lailah's--

00:03:31.130 --> 00:03:33.468
Or should I say,
my mom's footsteps,

00:03:33.552 --> 00:03:35.806
it might help me
figure things out.

00:03:35.890 --> 00:03:37.434
You believe Lailah
holds the secrets

00:03:37.518 --> 00:03:38.937
you wish to unlock?

00:03:39.021 --> 00:03:39.898
Yeah.

00:03:39.981 --> 00:03:42.027
The sword, and the Yesod shards.

00:03:42.110 --> 00:03:44.323
About Heaven and the demons.

00:03:44.406 --> 00:03:46.410
Hey, I'm not counting on
some big answer,

00:03:46.494 --> 00:03:47.705
but maybe I'll get lucky.

00:03:48.582 --> 00:03:51.337
Well, uh, is it okay
if I see you off?

00:03:51.420 --> 00:03:52.674
That's so sweet.

00:03:52.757 --> 00:03:55.220
Emerada's opening the Gate
Monday afternoon.

00:03:55.303 --> 00:03:57.642
I believe you'll still be
in school then.

00:03:57.725 --> 00:03:59.228
I appreciate it, though.

00:03:59.311 --> 00:04:00.355
Oh.

00:04:00.438 --> 00:04:01.399
Don't fret.

00:04:01.482 --> 00:04:03.236
I'll see her off for you.

00:04:04.488 --> 00:04:06.827
There's no need to be sad.

00:04:06.910 --> 00:04:09.874
The very latest I would get back
is the morning of the 12th.

00:04:10.668 --> 00:04:12.421
The 12th, huh?

00:04:12.505 --> 00:04:13.632
Yeah, that's right.

00:04:14.466 --> 00:04:17.013
Your joint birthday party
with Chi.

00:04:17.097 --> 00:04:18.141
[SUZUNO]
Ah, yes.

00:04:18.224 --> 00:04:20.228
I suppose your birthday
would be in the autumn

00:04:20.311 --> 00:04:22.149
by this world's calendar.

00:04:22.232 --> 00:04:24.153
♪

00:04:27.117 --> 00:04:28.662
[EMI]
I'm gonna be fine.

00:04:29.037 --> 00:04:31.626
I am the strongest hero
in history, you know?

00:04:31.710 --> 00:04:34.632
Plus, I won't try anything
too risky with the baby there.

00:04:34.716 --> 00:04:37.053
I'm basically going to clean up
my folks' old house.

00:04:37.513 --> 00:04:39.308
I'll come back soon.

00:04:39.391 --> 00:04:41.688
Okay, I trust you.

00:04:41.772 --> 00:04:43.149
While you're away,

00:04:43.232 --> 00:04:46.072
I should try and perfect
my "kid curry" recipe.

00:04:46.155 --> 00:04:47.449
It'll be a hit!

00:04:47.784 --> 00:04:49.411
Huh?

00:04:49.495 --> 00:04:52.417
Kid curry? No, don't eat kids.

00:04:52.502 --> 00:04:54.421
Nobody's eating kids, sleepy.

00:04:54.506 --> 00:04:56.510
Welp, it's time for beddy-bye.

00:04:59.808 --> 00:05:02.145
See you next week
for the party, Chiho.

00:05:02.229 --> 00:05:03.982
Bel, I'll message you later.

00:05:04.066 --> 00:05:05.736
Night-night, guys!

00:05:05.820 --> 00:05:08.116
Night, Dada! Night, Chi-mi!

00:05:08.199 --> 00:05:10.704
Night, Suzu-mi! Bye-bye!

00:05:10.788 --> 00:05:12.124
[door closes]

00:05:12.207 --> 00:05:13.209
[MAOU]
I'm home.

00:05:13.292 --> 00:05:15.421
[ASHIYA]
Looking radiant as always, Sire!

00:05:15.506 --> 00:05:17.593
Have you been huffing
cleaning supplies?

00:05:17.677 --> 00:05:21.016
Oh, please, I'm simply glad
to be rid of Emilia.

00:05:21.100 --> 00:05:22.477
A moment of peace!

00:05:23.689 --> 00:05:26.570
I've been holding on to this
for a special occasion!

00:05:26.653 --> 00:05:27.697
Let us splurge.

00:05:27.780 --> 00:05:30.118
And indulge in a feast
of grilled organ meats!

00:05:30.201 --> 00:05:31.370
Hey, boss,

00:05:31.453 --> 00:05:33.542
I messaged you asking
to bring me home some flan,

00:05:33.625 --> 00:05:34.586
did you miss it?

00:05:34.669 --> 00:05:36.088
Must have.

00:05:36.172 --> 00:05:37.257
Argh.

00:05:37.340 --> 00:05:38.217
And the one time

00:05:38.301 --> 00:05:40.598
that mom lets me get
a sweet little treat!

00:05:42.184 --> 00:05:43.604
[grunts]

00:05:43.687 --> 00:05:44.814
Is something wrong?

00:05:44.898 --> 00:05:46.860
Growling? Chill out.

00:05:46.943 --> 00:05:49.574
The second she leaves,
you'd blow our budget?

00:05:49.657 --> 00:05:52.580
I have been busting my ass
getting her to trust you jerks!

00:05:52.663 --> 00:05:53.832
Do you wanna prove her right

00:05:53.916 --> 00:05:55.711
that demons
need a babysitter?

00:05:55.794 --> 00:05:57.005
-[door slams]
-Be silent you fools,

00:05:57.088 --> 00:05:58.717
you're bothering the neighbor!

00:06:07.150 --> 00:06:08.612
[CHIHO]
It's that time.

00:06:12.536 --> 00:06:13.622
[ring clinks]

00:06:14.373 --> 00:06:17.045
When Miss Yusa passes
through the Gate,

00:06:17.128 --> 00:06:19.299
I wonder if it'll do something.

00:06:19.383 --> 00:06:20.594
[whirring]

00:06:20.678 --> 00:06:21.846
[gasps]

00:06:21.930 --> 00:06:26.355
♪

00:06:26.438 --> 00:06:28.317
-[gasps]
-[phone vibrating]

00:06:34.872 --> 00:06:35.874
Hmm.

00:06:39.841 --> 00:06:42.429
I hope Ente Isla's peaceful
for her.

00:06:42.513 --> 00:06:45.393
And she and Alas Ramus
get there safe.

00:06:57.501 --> 00:07:01.425
♪

00:07:08.481 --> 00:07:09.817
[ASHIYA]
Your Majesty,

00:07:09.901 --> 00:07:11.821
it's time you take a break
from your studies.

00:07:11.905 --> 00:07:13.950
Yeah, you're right.

00:07:14.034 --> 00:07:16.497
I can't believe the Devil
is asking the government

00:07:16.581 --> 00:07:18.459
for permission to do anything.

00:07:18.543 --> 00:07:20.463
Let alone to drive a moped.

00:07:20.547 --> 00:07:22.467
Silence, you ingrate!

00:07:22.551 --> 00:07:24.847
Don't discourage
your lord's efforts!

00:07:24.931 --> 00:07:26.810
Are you sure that
you wanna get the license

00:07:26.893 --> 00:07:28.145
and start delivering?

00:07:28.229 --> 00:07:30.609
I know you're MgRonald's
best boy and all,

00:07:30.692 --> 00:07:32.320
but are ya lookin'
for extra work?

00:07:32.403 --> 00:07:34.116
I've been getting
assigned shift manager

00:07:34.199 --> 00:07:35.869
more and more recently.

00:07:35.953 --> 00:07:38.415
I need to be ready to cover
if anyone's out.

00:07:38.499 --> 00:07:39.877
It's part of being responsible.

00:07:39.961 --> 00:07:42.716
Sire, your allegiance
is admirable!

00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:46.641
Thanks, but I'm just trying
to do my job, so.

00:07:46.724 --> 00:07:47.601
Huh?

00:07:52.235 --> 00:07:54.866
It would seem Emilia
hasn't returned just yet.

00:07:56.536 --> 00:07:58.080
How weird.

00:07:59.249 --> 00:08:01.629
[birds chirp]

00:08:08.100 --> 00:08:09.144
[knocks at door]

00:08:12.483 --> 00:08:13.737
Good day.

00:08:13.820 --> 00:08:15.908
Have you seen any sign of her?

00:08:16.826 --> 00:08:18.412
Still not back, huh?

00:08:19.122 --> 00:08:21.711
There's been no correspondence,
either.

00:08:21.794 --> 00:08:24.634
I thought
she might have phoned you, but.

00:08:24.717 --> 00:08:28.015
She would never reach out to us
over you or Chi.

00:08:28.098 --> 00:08:30.771
You should try
getting in contact with Emerada.

00:08:30.854 --> 00:08:33.400
I did try, and she's not
answering as well.

00:08:33.484 --> 00:08:34.612
[gasps]

00:08:34.695 --> 00:08:35.864
It's a dance.

00:08:35.948 --> 00:08:37.660
Ente Isla's in turmoil.

00:08:38.494 --> 00:08:40.456
Send out too many idea links,

00:08:40.540 --> 00:08:42.878
and the wrong person
might detect them.

00:08:42.962 --> 00:08:45.634
Yeah, like our old buddy Olba.

00:08:45.717 --> 00:08:49.057
Emilia has bested your armies
and archangels.

00:08:49.140 --> 00:08:52.146
So an incident that would
warrant radio silence from her

00:08:52.230 --> 00:08:54.442
would surely be apocalyptic.

00:08:54.527 --> 00:08:57.156
If she is wounded,
Ente Isla is done for.

00:08:58.158 --> 00:09:01.541
When you get fully powered up,
you can open gates, right?

00:09:02.041 --> 00:09:03.294
Here's my idea.

00:09:03.712 --> 00:09:06.634
Get jacked up with Suz's
celestial force juice again

00:09:06.718 --> 00:09:08.513
and get your mojo back.

00:09:08.597 --> 00:09:09.472
Boom.

00:09:09.557 --> 00:09:12.020
Then you can check out Ente Isla
for yourself.

00:09:12.103 --> 00:09:13.523
That's not gonna work.

00:09:13.898 --> 00:09:15.527
[SUZUNO]
He is correct.

00:09:15.610 --> 00:09:17.740
I can't do it without Emilia.

00:09:17.823 --> 00:09:20.286
I doubt I possess
half the power she has.

00:09:20.369 --> 00:09:22.541
It wouldn't be enough
to overload him.

00:09:22.625 --> 00:09:24.377
Well, that blows.

00:09:24.461 --> 00:09:26.549
I thought
I was really doing something.

00:09:26.633 --> 00:09:28.177
Wait a sec,

00:09:28.260 --> 00:09:31.058
are you suggesting
I need to go save her?

00:09:31.141 --> 00:09:32.686
You ordered flan when she left,

00:09:32.770 --> 00:09:34.314
and we don't even know
if she's hurt.

00:09:34.940 --> 00:09:37.529
At the heart of all this,
she and I are enemies.

00:09:37.613 --> 00:09:38.447
I don't give a damn

00:09:38.531 --> 00:09:40.702
what the humans
in Ente Isla are doing.

00:09:40.786 --> 00:09:42.998
If they're duking it out
in world war whatever,

00:09:43.082 --> 00:09:44.167
let 'em fight.

00:09:45.461 --> 00:09:48.133
Even if Emi is in trouble
over there.

00:09:48.217 --> 00:09:50.137
There's nothing
that I can do here.

00:09:50.221 --> 00:09:52.475
And regardless,
it isn't my concern.

00:09:52.559 --> 00:09:54.605
But Satan, you don't...

00:09:54.689 --> 00:09:55.690
[exhales]

00:09:56.483 --> 00:09:57.736
That's all I have to say.

00:09:58.278 --> 00:09:59.364
If she doesn't show up,

00:09:59.447 --> 00:10:01.118
the party will
be canceled, right?

00:10:01.201 --> 00:10:04.625
I've gotta study for my moped
license test tomorrow.

00:10:05.961 --> 00:10:07.506
Tell me.

00:10:07.589 --> 00:10:09.467
What if Chiho approached you?

00:10:09.552 --> 00:10:10.887
Would your tune change?

00:10:10.971 --> 00:10:11.889
[gasps]

00:10:13.434 --> 00:10:15.605
I might word it more gently,

00:10:15.689 --> 00:10:17.316
but I'd tell her the same.

00:10:18.193 --> 00:10:20.406
-[CHIHO] Mister Maou.
-[MAOU gasps]

00:10:20.489 --> 00:10:24.414
♪

00:10:24.497 --> 00:10:25.834
It's Miss Sasaki.

00:10:25.917 --> 00:10:28.046
Damn,
so we're playing dirty now.

00:10:28.130 --> 00:10:29.382
Chi, I...

00:10:29.925 --> 00:10:30.802
Don't lie.

00:10:30.886 --> 00:10:33.140
I know you would never ever
break a promise.

00:10:33.223 --> 00:10:35.019
You're too good of a guy
to do that.

00:10:35.102 --> 00:10:36.229
[gasps]

00:10:36.313 --> 00:10:40.279
[CHIHO] When I got kidnapped,
do you remember what you said?

00:10:40.362 --> 00:10:42.743
The amazing present
that you gave us?

00:10:44.370 --> 00:10:46.333
You said that me, Miss Suzuno,

00:10:46.416 --> 00:10:49.255
and Miss Yusa were
all your generals now.

00:10:50.299 --> 00:10:52.513
You promised to show us
a new world

00:10:52.596 --> 00:10:54.265
if we stayed by your side.

00:10:54.349 --> 00:10:55.560
You poor dear.

00:10:55.644 --> 00:10:58.942
Alas Ramus is in that big,
scary place with her.

00:10:59.025 --> 00:11:00.194
Don't pretend.

00:11:00.277 --> 00:11:03.075
I know that you're worried
about both of them.

00:11:03.158 --> 00:11:05.664
It's hard for all of us.

00:11:05.747 --> 00:11:06.958
So don't lie.

00:11:07.041 --> 00:11:08.586
-[sobs]
-There, there.

00:11:09.797 --> 00:11:10.966
This was my plan.

00:11:11.049 --> 00:11:12.260
Don't blame Miss Suzuno,

00:11:12.343 --> 00:11:14.765
because I'm the one
who asked her to do it.

00:11:14.849 --> 00:11:16.226
I tricked you guys.

00:11:16.309 --> 00:11:17.436
I'm sorry.

00:11:20.944 --> 00:11:24.033
I'll evaluate the best course
of action on my end.

00:11:24.117 --> 00:11:25.202
Excuse me.

00:11:32.008 --> 00:11:32.968
[MAOU grunts]

00:11:33.385 --> 00:11:34.429
Shit!

00:11:37.476 --> 00:11:39.565
[ASHIYA]
Your Majesty, if I may--

00:11:39.648 --> 00:11:40.734
[MAOU]
Oh, great.

00:11:40.817 --> 00:11:42.988
You gonna tell me
to go save Emi, too?

00:11:43.906 --> 00:11:44.950
[ASHIYA]
No.

00:11:45.034 --> 00:11:46.411
Because in my humble opinion,

00:11:46.494 --> 00:11:48.415
we have far graver matters
at hand.

00:11:48.498 --> 00:11:49.710
Huh?

00:11:49.793 --> 00:11:51.087
She is strong.

00:11:51.171 --> 00:11:53.926
Even our mightiest troops
couldn't defeat her.

00:11:54.010 --> 00:11:56.222
But if humans are warring

00:11:56.306 --> 00:11:58.310
with their own kind
in Ente Isla,

00:11:58.393 --> 00:12:01.358
and anything poses a threat
to Emilia,

00:12:01.441 --> 00:12:04.322
that indicates to us
someone is not fighting fair.

00:12:05.282 --> 00:12:08.080
She has enemies in the Church
and in Heaven itself.

00:12:08.163 --> 00:12:09.958
Now in the Malebranche, as well.

00:12:10.042 --> 00:12:11.461
She is a target.

00:12:12.421 --> 00:12:14.927
If any of them are keen
on her whereabouts,

00:12:15.010 --> 00:12:16.889
and see she's in Ente Isla,

00:12:17.724 --> 00:12:19.477
they'll use this time to attack.

00:12:19.812 --> 00:12:22.358
[MAOU] No way
they could beat her in a fight.

00:12:22.441 --> 00:12:26.116
But maybe,
they could take hostages.

00:12:27.159 --> 00:12:29.163
You think somebody got Emerada?

00:12:29.247 --> 00:12:31.711
It needn't be someone so strong.

00:12:31.794 --> 00:12:33.673
Anyone she cares for would do.

00:12:34.633 --> 00:12:37.471
A person who's well-being
would make her think twice.

00:12:37.556 --> 00:12:39.308
The list is near endless.

00:12:39.392 --> 00:12:40.310
I guess,

00:12:40.394 --> 00:12:43.693
but why would the Ente Islans
go that far to hurt her?

00:12:43.776 --> 00:12:46.281
She's the freakin' hero
who saved their world.

00:12:48.076 --> 00:12:50.414
What you sent Farfarello
home with,

00:12:50.497 --> 00:12:54.005
the news of Bel and Emilia
becoming your demon generals.

00:12:54.088 --> 00:12:55.925
I fear that it was unwise.

00:12:56.009 --> 00:12:58.931
Yeah, I mean, I got carried away
in the moment for sure,

00:12:59.015 --> 00:13:01.436
but I did all that
to protect Chi

00:13:01.520 --> 00:13:03.398
and to keep
any of Farfarello's friends

00:13:03.482 --> 00:13:04.985
from showing up in Japan.

00:13:07.364 --> 00:13:08.492
[MAOU gasps]

00:13:09.661 --> 00:13:10.496
Hold on!

00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:11.707
Oh, crap.

00:13:11.791 --> 00:13:13.795
You think that news made it back
to the humans?

00:13:13.878 --> 00:13:16.257
And now Emi and Suz
are traitors?

00:13:17.009 --> 00:13:19.138
Some have always harbored doubt.

00:13:19.222 --> 00:13:22.061
I'm sure they'll use this
to try to bring down the Hero.

00:13:22.144 --> 00:13:24.691
[MAOU]
And Emi and Suz realized that?

00:13:24.775 --> 00:13:26.570
[ASHIYA]
I assume so, yes.

00:13:26.654 --> 00:13:28.533
But they were willing
to take on the danger

00:13:28.616 --> 00:13:30.369
for Miss Sasaki's sake.

00:13:30.452 --> 00:13:32.582
Didn't Emilia herself
mention returning home

00:13:32.666 --> 00:13:34.795
because she was tired
of playing defense here?

00:13:36.297 --> 00:13:39.387
I believe she and Bel
work rather hard

00:13:39.470 --> 00:13:41.099
to protect our status quo.

00:13:41.976 --> 00:13:43.521
They want to preserve
this lifestyle

00:13:43.604 --> 00:13:47.027
where, as incompatible and
prone to bickering as we are,

00:13:47.111 --> 00:13:48.614
we sit at the same table.

00:13:49.031 --> 00:13:51.119
Where the hell
did I put that thing?

00:13:51.202 --> 00:13:53.164
I know I left it in here
last time.

00:13:53.248 --> 00:13:55.294
It's no time
for aimless rummaging!

00:13:55.377 --> 00:13:57.172
The adults are having
a discussion!

00:13:57.256 --> 00:13:58.759
He's fine.

00:13:58.843 --> 00:14:00.345
Well, go on.

00:14:00.429 --> 00:14:01.724
Right!

00:14:01.807 --> 00:14:05.314
On a human battlefield,
Emilia will always prevail.

00:14:05.397 --> 00:14:07.652
That said,
certain forces value her

00:14:07.736 --> 00:14:09.698
for more
than her prowess in combat.

00:14:11.577 --> 00:14:13.204
[MAOU]
The angels?

00:14:13.288 --> 00:14:15.083
That's all speculation.

00:14:15.167 --> 00:14:18.256
You guys are just too used
to these cushy, Japanese trains

00:14:18.340 --> 00:14:19.927
that are always on schedule.

00:14:20.010 --> 00:14:21.597
People can run late, you know.

00:14:22.097 --> 00:14:24.477
That's weirdly optimistic
coming for you.

00:14:24.561 --> 00:14:27.066
Even if there's a hostage,
Emi's fine.

00:14:27.149 --> 00:14:29.111
There's no one there or here
for that matter

00:14:29.195 --> 00:14:30.072
who could kill her.

00:14:30.155 --> 00:14:33.078
Even worst-case scenario,
she's still alive.

00:14:33.161 --> 00:14:34.790
That means baby's chilling.

00:14:34.873 --> 00:14:36.502
Not that she can't kick ass,
too.

00:14:37.419 --> 00:14:39.173
If Emi was in some
kinda trouble,

00:14:39.256 --> 00:14:41.469
she wouldn't want
your help anyway, dude.

00:14:43.975 --> 00:14:45.728
Hey, guys, listen.

00:14:45.812 --> 00:14:46.730
Sire!

00:14:46.814 --> 00:14:47.732
Hm?

00:14:48.274 --> 00:14:49.861
Thanks a lot.

00:14:49.945 --> 00:14:52.826
You both calmed me down
and I needed that.

00:14:52.909 --> 00:14:54.997
For now, I'll concentrate
on my test.

00:14:55.790 --> 00:14:59.715
Whenever she does get back,
I'll rub my license in her face,

00:14:59.798 --> 00:15:01.467
"try being late with this!"

00:15:04.933 --> 00:15:07.021
[ASHIYA]
May you return victorious, Sire.

00:15:07.104 --> 00:15:08.440
It's not war, man.

00:15:08.524 --> 00:15:10.068
Just a license.

00:15:10.152 --> 00:15:11.530
-Oops!
-[thuds]

00:15:12.782 --> 00:15:13.617
[MAOU chuckles]

00:15:13.701 --> 00:15:16.330
Maybe I'm a little more nervous
than I let on.

00:15:16.414 --> 00:15:19.378
It's often beneficial
to be on your toes.

00:15:19.462 --> 00:15:21.215
I'm sure you'll pass the test.

00:15:21.299 --> 00:15:23.804
As always, you have
my undying faith, Sire.

00:15:23.888 --> 00:15:25.182
Welp, see ya.

00:15:25.265 --> 00:15:28.313
♪

00:15:32.906 --> 00:15:35.368
[ANNOUNCER 17A]
<i>Stopping at Tenmondai-mae.</i>

00:15:36.747 --> 00:15:39.711
[TSUBASA]
[panting] Look, Dad, we made it!

00:15:39.795 --> 00:15:42.257
Don't be a slow poke!
Hurry, hurry!

00:15:43.761 --> 00:15:45.807
[brakes hissing]

00:15:49.940 --> 00:15:51.359
Huh?

00:15:52.486 --> 00:15:53.614
[TSUBASA sniffing]

00:15:53.697 --> 00:15:54.616
Huh?

00:15:56.703 --> 00:15:57.872
Whoa, hey!

00:15:57.956 --> 00:16:00.252
Oh, I'm terribly sorry, sir.

00:16:00.335 --> 00:16:01.880
[MAOU]
These ain't locals.

00:16:01.964 --> 00:16:04.218
[HIROSHI]
Tsubasa, apologize to him.

00:16:04.301 --> 00:16:05.972
Okay! I will, Dad!

00:16:06.055 --> 00:16:07.224
Sorry, Mister!

00:16:15.575 --> 00:16:16.743
[MAOU sighs]

00:16:17.871 --> 00:16:20.208
[ANNOUNCER 17A]
<i>Next stop, Shikenjo-Seimon.</i>

00:16:20.292 --> 00:16:22.755
<i>Exit here for the
Driver's License Headquarters--</i>

00:16:22.839 --> 00:16:24.634
-[MAOU] Well, that's me!
-Huh?

00:16:24.718 --> 00:16:26.638
[ANNOUNCER 17A]
<i>Thank you for traveling with us.</i>

00:16:30.228 --> 00:16:31.063
Perfect.

00:16:31.147 --> 00:16:32.984
They should be dry by afternoon.

00:16:33.067 --> 00:16:34.153
-[RIKA] Uh?
-Huh?

00:16:35.238 --> 00:16:36.658
[ASHIYA]
Miss Suzuki?

00:16:39.205 --> 00:16:41.668
[MAOU] There's still some time
before my turn.

00:16:42.754 --> 00:16:44.048
Hmmm.

00:16:45.801 --> 00:16:47.429
[TSUBASA]
You're here for a license, too?

00:16:47.513 --> 00:16:48.389
[MAOU gasps]

00:16:48.473 --> 00:16:50.686
How many times have you tested?

00:16:50.770 --> 00:16:53.274
This is going to be me
and Dad's tenth time!

00:16:53.358 --> 00:16:54.736
The big "one-zero!"

00:16:54.819 --> 00:16:55.655
Tenth?

00:16:55.738 --> 00:16:57.867
Uh, this is only
my first attempt.

00:16:57.951 --> 00:17:00.205
[TSUBASA] My Dad can't read
kanji too good yet.

00:17:00.288 --> 00:17:02.877
So, I came to be
his super-reader-helper!

00:17:04.338 --> 00:17:05.925
[MAOU]
Uh, that's nice.

00:17:06.008 --> 00:17:08.096
Would be a lot nicer
if I'd studied.

00:17:09.056 --> 00:17:10.350
[MAOU]
Good luck to ya.

00:17:11.853 --> 00:17:13.774
Got a name? What is it?

00:17:14.651 --> 00:17:16.153
Yeah, uh...

00:17:16.237 --> 00:17:17.322
Mine's Ah--

00:17:17.406 --> 00:17:19.536
I mean, mine's Tsubasa Satou.

00:17:19.619 --> 00:17:20.788
Huh?

00:17:20.871 --> 00:17:22.792
[TSUBASA]
Dad's Hiroshi Satou!

00:17:24.044 --> 00:17:25.213
Cool.

00:17:25.297 --> 00:17:27.259
Nice to meet you. I'm, Maou.

00:17:27.342 --> 00:17:30.015
Are you some kinda demon king?

00:17:30.098 --> 00:17:31.017
[thuds]

00:17:31.100 --> 00:17:33.522
[MAOU gasps]

00:17:37.112 --> 00:17:40.160
Sounds like the name
of a final boss in a video game!

00:17:40.243 --> 00:17:42.915
I'm sorry, no cool demon kings
around here.

00:17:44.919 --> 00:17:45.755
[sniffing]

00:17:45.838 --> 00:17:46.673
[shrieks]

00:17:46.757 --> 00:17:49.178
You can't go sniffing strangers!

00:17:49.261 --> 00:17:50.472
Be careful.

00:17:50.556 --> 00:17:52.309
You don't want to stand out.

00:17:52.392 --> 00:17:53.311
His smell,

00:17:53.394 --> 00:17:55.691
it's almost like I remember it
from somewhere.

00:17:56.442 --> 00:17:57.987
It was warm and cozy.

00:17:58.071 --> 00:18:00.241
A place from a long time ago.

00:18:03.791 --> 00:18:05.711
[bicycle bells rings]

00:18:06.128 --> 00:18:08.216
[RIKA giggles]

00:18:14.478 --> 00:18:15.480
[ASHIYA]
Have some tea.

00:18:15.564 --> 00:18:17.484
[RIKA]
Oh, thank you.

00:18:17.568 --> 00:18:19.989
How were you able
to locate our domicile?

00:18:20.073 --> 00:18:22.369
I exchanged contact info
with Suzuno

00:18:22.452 --> 00:18:24.206
when we went TV shopping.

00:18:24.289 --> 00:18:26.878
Don't get me wrong, I felt bad
about showing up at your place

00:18:26.962 --> 00:18:29.133
without giving you
a good heads up.

00:18:29.216 --> 00:18:32.013
But, uh, I felt like I had
to do something.

00:18:33.057 --> 00:18:34.769
You're here about Yusa.

00:18:34.853 --> 00:18:36.230
Mmm-hmm.

00:18:36.313 --> 00:18:39.027
So, please, tell me that
you've heard from her.

00:18:39.571 --> 00:18:41.742
We can't get
a single message through.

00:18:41.825 --> 00:18:43.829
None of them are even
showing up as "read."

00:18:43.912 --> 00:18:45.875
I went to her place,
but, nothing.

00:18:45.958 --> 00:18:47.043
She's been gone from work

00:18:47.127 --> 00:18:49.131
without taking leave
for a long time now.

00:18:50.091 --> 00:18:51.720
Her folks, they don't live here,

00:18:51.803 --> 00:18:53.347
they're pretty far abroad,
right?

00:18:53.431 --> 00:18:54.893
Yes, that's right.

00:18:54.976 --> 00:18:57.189
She said
she had some family business.

00:18:57.272 --> 00:18:58.942
But because her family is so far

00:18:59.026 --> 00:19:00.779
and most of her friends
are from work,

00:19:00.863 --> 00:19:01.740
we're all worried

00:19:01.823 --> 00:19:03.702
that if something bad
had happened to her,

00:19:03.786 --> 00:19:05.246
we wouldn't hear about it
soon enough

00:19:05.330 --> 00:19:07.417
to help her out
when she needs us most.

00:19:07.919 --> 00:19:09.631
I do apologize.

00:19:09.714 --> 00:19:12.678
But I'm afraid none of us here
know anything more than you.

00:19:12.762 --> 00:19:15.935
Maybe we should start
to consider calling the police.

00:19:16.018 --> 00:19:18.397
Friends aren't supposed
to drop all contact with you

00:19:18.481 --> 00:19:20.193
-for an entire week!
-[ALL] Huh?

00:19:20.819 --> 00:19:23.617
Pardon, will you repeat
that time frame?

00:19:23.700 --> 00:19:25.245
When did you two last talk?

00:19:25.328 --> 00:19:27.415
[RIKA]
I told you, it's been a week.

00:19:27.499 --> 00:19:29.002
[SUZUNO]
U-Understood, thank you.

00:19:29.086 --> 00:19:30.631
That's valuable information.

00:19:30.714 --> 00:19:33.804
Do you recall the exact date
and time you heard from her?

00:19:33.887 --> 00:19:35.975
It was sometime
last Friday night.

00:19:36.058 --> 00:19:38.605
[SUZUNO] Uh, we haven't heard
from her in two weeks.

00:19:38.689 --> 00:19:41.235
We lost touch with her
the Friday before last.

00:19:41.318 --> 00:19:42.989
Or rather, that's the date
she told us

00:19:43.072 --> 00:19:44.784
we could anticipate her return.

00:19:44.867 --> 00:19:46.871
I suppose
it's been three weeks now.

00:19:46.955 --> 00:19:47.915
[RIKA]
Really?

00:19:47.999 --> 00:19:49.669
Did she call, or what?

00:19:49.752 --> 00:19:51.255
[RIKA]
Yeah, she did.

00:19:51.338 --> 00:19:52.382
I'll show you.

00:19:53.844 --> 00:19:55.263
[SUZUNO]
An unknown number?

00:19:56.181 --> 00:19:59.062
Could it have been someone
posing as her, instead?

00:19:59.146 --> 00:20:00.315
Not a chance.

00:20:00.398 --> 00:20:01.735
It was Emi's voice.

00:20:01.818 --> 00:20:02.945
Plus, she said her name

00:20:03.029 --> 00:20:04.991
before I could even get
a hello in.

00:20:05.074 --> 00:20:07.370
She sounded the same
as she always does.

00:20:07.454 --> 00:20:08.665
Not to pry,

00:20:08.749 --> 00:20:11.170
but what was it that you spoke
with her about?

00:20:11.253 --> 00:20:13.424
Uh, she just wanted to know

00:20:13.508 --> 00:20:15.178
if she could swap shifts
with me.

00:20:15.261 --> 00:20:17.182
-[ASHIYA, SUZUNO] Huh?
-Hmm.

00:20:17.265 --> 00:20:19.896
♪

00:20:19.979 --> 00:20:20.981
Uh-oh.

00:20:21.065 --> 00:20:22.317
[KAORI]
What is it?

00:20:22.943 --> 00:20:25.323
[CHIHO] It was so sunny
just a minute ago.

00:20:25.406 --> 00:20:26.868
[KAORI] The forecast said
it wouldn't rain

00:20:26.951 --> 00:20:28.245
until the afternoon.

00:20:29.791 --> 00:20:31.836
[URUSHIHARA]
Anything unusual about the call?

00:20:32.588 --> 00:20:35.678
She might've sounded a little
bit far away from the phone.

00:20:35.761 --> 00:20:37.807
And her voice
was kind of breathy.

00:20:37.890 --> 00:20:40.395
She was talking faster
than usual, too.

00:20:40.478 --> 00:20:43.067
But she's dealing
with some tricky stuff overseas,

00:20:43.150 --> 00:20:44.862
so I didn't think much of it.

00:20:44.946 --> 00:20:47.200
Curious, what caused her
to choose Rika?

00:20:47.283 --> 00:20:48.119
Huh?

00:20:48.202 --> 00:20:49.998
[rain pattering]

00:20:50.081 --> 00:20:52.753
Excuse me,
there's laundry to save.

00:20:52.837 --> 00:20:53.755
[SUZUNO]
Oh, dear.

00:20:53.839 --> 00:20:55.884
I believe I left my window open.

00:20:55.968 --> 00:20:57.137
One moment, please.

00:20:57.220 --> 00:20:59.349
You live here. You should help.

00:20:59.433 --> 00:21:00.602
Fine.

00:21:04.610 --> 00:21:06.030
Hm?

00:21:06.113 --> 00:21:07.449
A lady's present!

00:21:07.533 --> 00:21:09.912
Have some decency, please!

00:21:09.996 --> 00:21:11.498
I've seen undies before!

00:21:11.583 --> 00:21:12.500
-It's no sweat.
-[window closes]

00:21:12.585 --> 00:21:14.296
Oh, wowza.

00:21:14.379 --> 00:21:15.674
Look at that sky.

00:21:15.758 --> 00:21:18.095
I don't think the weather report
predicted this much rain.

00:21:18.179 --> 00:21:19.306
[door slams]

00:21:19.389 --> 00:21:20.433
Emergency!

00:21:20.517 --> 00:21:21.686
[gasps] What happened?

00:21:21.770 --> 00:21:22.938
Take this.

00:21:23.022 --> 00:21:24.859
Uh, this is...

00:21:25.819 --> 00:21:27.322
Y'all's booster, right?

00:21:28.032 --> 00:21:29.952
An SOS. From Chiho.

00:21:30.036 --> 00:21:32.332
A successful idea link.

00:21:32.415 --> 00:21:34.921
Right now,
you're our only option.

00:21:35.004 --> 00:21:35.964
Let's fly.

00:21:36.048 --> 00:21:37.802
Do you know
where she goes to school?

00:21:37.885 --> 00:21:39.639
Maybe. I hope.

00:21:40.389 --> 00:21:42.393
It's Sasahata North, right?

00:21:42.477 --> 00:21:44.816
I'm pretty confident
I know where that is.

00:21:44.899 --> 00:21:45.984
Wait, Chi?

00:21:46.068 --> 00:21:47.362
The same one I know?

00:21:47.445 --> 00:21:49.575
Go! She's in need! Hurry!

00:21:49.659 --> 00:21:50.869
In time, Rika,

00:21:50.953 --> 00:21:54.292
I shall explain this all to you,
but for now, we must depart.

00:21:54.376 --> 00:21:55.879
The damage could be great.

00:21:55.963 --> 00:21:58.844
It may very well extend
beyond her school by now.

00:21:59.512 --> 00:22:00.556
[URUSHIHARA, SUZUNO]
Hmm.

00:22:00.639 --> 00:22:01.850
[URUSHIHARA, SUZUNO gulping]

00:22:03.435 --> 00:22:05.356
[wind howling]

00:22:05.439 --> 00:22:07.611
[SUZUNO, URUSHIHARA]
Divine Boots of Light!

00:22:07.695 --> 00:22:09.615
[whooshing]

00:22:09.699 --> 00:22:12.621
♪

00:22:12.705 --> 00:22:15.544
-[ASHIYA sighs]
-Huh?

